
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-huitema-6man-random-addresses-03.txt'>
    <title>"Implications of Randomized Link Layers Addresses for IPv6 Address Assignment", Christian Huitema</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-huitema-6man-random-addresses-03.txt</link>
    <description>Hosts may assign random link-layer addresses to network interfaces in an attempt to increase privacy and reduce trackability.  Careless assignment of IPv6 addresses may negate the privacy advantages of random link-layer addresses.  We propose simple solutions to ensure that IPv6 addresses do change whenever the link layer addresses change.</description>
    <dc:date>2016-03-02T08:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
